<figureCitation box="[420,480,1498,1521]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[223,1348,199,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[212,1360,194,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hoedillus sexpunctatus Simon, 1898, male. A. Habitus. B – F. Right pedipalpus; B. Retrolateral view; C. Ventral view; D. Prolateral view; E. Tibia ventral view; F. Pedipalpus, dorsal view, highlighting dorsal cymbial scopula. Con—conductor, Em—embolus, MA—median apophysis, TA—tegular apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262395/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">
