<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,701,1972]" box="[199,820,1533,1556]" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Ventrally with opisthosoma light yellow-brown, maculate.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,701,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">
Pedipalpus trochanter, femur, and patella light yellow; tibia orange-brown, large RTA placed on base of tibia, elongate, narrowed distally, with proximally placed spur on ventral surface, anterior edge of proximal half serrate, with large, thick dorsal spine on distal region of RTA (
<figureCitation box="[679,738,1637,1660]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[223,1348,199,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[212,1360,194,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hoedillus sexpunctatus Simon, 1898, male. A. Habitus. B – F. Right pedipalpus; B. Retrolateral view; C. Ventral view; D. Prolateral view; E. Tibia ventral view; F. Pedipalpus, dorsal view, highlighting dorsal cymbial scopula. Con—conductor, Em—embolus, MA—median apophysis, TA—tegular apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262395/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[729,738,1637,1660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="448" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B–F). Dense oval brush of thicker curved setae on dorsal surface of cymbium (
<figureCitation box="[306,370,1672,1695]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[223,1348,199,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[212,1360,194,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hoedillus sexpunctatus Simon, 1898, male. A. Habitus. B – F. Right pedipalpus; B. Retrolateral view; C. Ventral view; D. Prolateral view; E. Tibia ventral view; F. Pedipalpus, dorsal view, highlighting dorsal cymbial scopula. Con—conductor, Em—embolus, MA—median apophysis, TA—tegular apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262395/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[361,370,1672,1695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="448" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B–D, F); pedipalpus bulb with sperm duct visible; median apophysis short, curving medially; embolus, curving laterally into transparent conductor, blunt tegular apophysis projected antero-ventrally from middle of tegulum, most easily seen in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[600,658,1741,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[223,1348,199,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[212,1360,194,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hoedillus sexpunctatus Simon, 1898, male. A. Habitus. B – F. Right pedipalpus; B. Retrolateral view; C. Ventral view; D. Prolateral view; E. Tibia ventral view; F. Pedipalpus, dorsal view, highlighting dorsal cymbial scopula. Con—conductor, Em—embolus, MA—median apophysis, TA—tegular apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262395/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[649,658,1741,1764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="448" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B–D).
</paragraph>
